<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-872] Parameters added to a VFS endpoint are added to the reply file name also</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-872</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we want to write to a file and we want to append to that file, VFS endpoint will look like below.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;address uri=&quot;vfs:&lt;a href=&quot;file:///home/amila/test/out/response.xml?transport.vfs.Append=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:///home/amila/test/out/response.xml?transport.vfs.Append=true&lt;/a&gt;&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Append works only when the parameter is added as shown above. But then, the response file name becomes &quot;response.xml?transport.vfs.Append=true&quot;. This is because the parameters being not considered when getting the file path.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a patch for this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
